Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addHierInst(25.10)                                          addHierInst(25.10)

Name
       addHierInst - Adds a hierarchical module to the design

Syntax
       addHierInst

       [-help]

       -cell <cellName >[-moduleBased <parentModuleName>]

       {-hinst <hinstName> | -module <moduleName>}

       Adds a hierarchical module to the design.

       You can use this command after importing a design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each addHierInst parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the  man  command:

              man addHierInst

       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the master of the module. Innovus creates a new, empty
              master if the cell name is new.

       -hinst <hinstName>
              Specifies the name of the module instance to add.

       -module <moduleName>
              Specifies the name of the module instance to add.

              Note: There is no difference between  -module  and  -hinst.  You
              should use -module for backward compatibility. It is recommended
              to use -hinst.

       -moduleBased <parentModuleName>
              Allows  the  addition of a new hierarchical instance into a Ver-
              ilog module which is instantiated multiple times.

Examples
              * The   following   command   adds   a   hierarchical   instance
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/spare  of  module type sparemodule to
                the design, here DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST should be an  exist-
                ing hierarchical instance in the design:

                addHierInst          -cell          sparemodule         -hinst
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/spare

              * The following commands create a new  module  modA  and  hinsts
                inst_modA and inst_modA_clone whose master cell is modA:

                addHierInst -cell modA -hinst inst_modA

                addHierInst -cell modA -hinst inst_modA_clone

                The resulting Verilog netlist would have:

                module modA();

                endmodule

                modA inst_modA();

                modA inst_modA_clone();

